---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="uses" description="Hardware, software, and tools I use">
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>uses</h1>
    <p>
      This page is a living document of the hardware, software, and tools that power my daily workflow. Inspired by the
      {" "}<a href="https://uses.tech">uses.tech</a> movement, I'm sharing my setup to help others discover new tools and
      make informed decisions about their own setups.
    </p>
  </header>
  <section class="uses-copy">
    <h2>Hardware</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong><a href="https://www.apple.com/macbook-pro/">MacBook Pro 16&quot;</a></strong> — My primary development machine
        with M1 Pro chip. Perfect for running Docker containers, heavy IDE workloads, and multitasking across multiple projects.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Magic Keyboard</strong> — Apple's wireless keyboard for clean desk setup. The low-profile keys are great for
        long coding sessions.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>LG UltraWide Monitor 34&quot;</strong> — Curved ultrawide display that provides ample screen real estate for
        side-by-side code editing and documentation.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sony WH-1000XM4</strong> — Noise-cancelling headphones essential for focused deep work sessions. Battery life
        lasts through multiple workdays.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Herman Miller Aeron Chair</strong> — Ergonomic office chair that keeps me comfortable during long coding sessions.
        Worth the investment for back health.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
